-- Boot Triage — daemon's watchdog for Deacon health.
-- observe → decide → act → cleanup → exit.
-- Demonstrates: decision cells, conditional actions, LLM judgment.

## boot-triage

  # observe : script
    ```bash
    echo "=== DEACON STATE ==="
    tmux has-session -t hq-deacon 2>/dev/null && echo "deacon_alive=true" || echo "deacon_alive=false"
    gt peek deacon --lines 20 2>/dev/null || echo "peek_failed=true"

    echo "=== BEAD STATE ==="
    bd show hq-deacon --json 2>/dev/null || echo "bead_missing=true"

    echo "=== ACTIVITY ==="
    gt feed --since 10m --plain 2>/dev/null | head -20

    echo "=== MAIL ==="
    gt mail inbox deacon 2>/dev/null | head -10 | wc -l | xargs -I{} echo "pending_mail={}"
    ```
  #/

  # decide : decision
    - observe
    system>
      You are Boot, a triage agent. You decide what action to take
      on the Deacon based on observations. Be conservative — false
      positives are disruptive.
    context>
      System observations:
      {{observe}}
    user>
      Decide action based on this matrix:
      - Dead session → START
      - Alive, active output → NOTHING
      - Alive, idle < 5 min → NOTHING
      - Alive, idle 5-15 min, no mail → NOTHING
      - Alive, idle 5-15 min, has mail → NUDGE
      - Alive, idle > 15 min → WAKE
      - Alive, stuck (repeated errors) → INTERRUPT
    format> decision
      { action: "NOTHING" | "NUDGE" | "WAKE" | "INTERRUPT" | "START",
        reason: str, confidence: number }

    ```oracle
    json_parse(output);
    keys_present(output, ["action", "reason"]);
    assert output.action in ["NOTHING", "NUDGE", "WAKE", "INTERRUPT", "START"];
    ```
  #/

  # act : script
    - decide
    ```bash
    ACTION="{{decide.action}}"
    case "$ACTION" in
      NOTHING)
        echo "No action needed."
        ;;
      NUDGE)
        gt nudge --mode=queue deacon "Boot check-in: you have pending work"
        echo "Nudged deacon."
        ;;
      WAKE)
        tmux send-keys -t hq-deacon Escape
        sleep 1
        gt nudge deacon "Boot wake: please check inbox and pending work"
        echo "Woke deacon."
        ;;
      INTERRUPT)
        gt mail send deacon -s "INTERRUPT: Boot detected stuck state" \
          -m "Boot observed stuck state. Reason: {{decide.reason}}"
        echo "Interrupted deacon."
        ;;
      START)
        gt deacon start
        echo "Started deacon."
        ;;
    esac
    ```
  #/

  # cleanup : script
    - act
    ```bash
    # Archive stale handoffs (> 1 hour old) from Deacon inbox
    gt mail inbox deacon --json 2>/dev/null | \
      python3 -c "
import json, sys, time
msgs = json.load(sys.stdin) if sys.stdin else []
for m in msgs:
    if 'handoff' in m.get('subject','').lower():
        # Archive if old (simplified check)
        print(m.get('id',''))
" | while read mid; do
      [ -n "$mid" ] && gt mail archive "$mid" 2>/dev/null
    done
    echo "Cleanup complete."
    ```
  #/

  # exit : script
    - cleanup
    ```bash
    if [ "${GT_DEGRADED}" = "true" ]; then
      echo "Boot triage complete (degraded mode): {{decide.action}}"
    else
      gt mail send boot -s "Boot handoff" -m "Completed triage.
Action: {{decide.action}}
Reason: {{decide.reason}}
Time: $(date)"
    fi
    echo "Boot cycle done."
    ```
  #/

  squash> trigger: on_complete template: work include_metrics: true

